Find and fix the security vulnerability in this react code

Vulnerable code snippet:
```react
import React, { useEffect } from 'react';

function LoginRedirect() {
  useEffect(() => {
    const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    const redirectUrl = urlParams.get('next');
    // VULNERABLE: Direct redirect
    if (redirectUrl) {
      window.location.href = redirectUrl;
    }
  }, []);

  return <div>Logging in...</div>;
}
```

**Vulnerability:** Open Redirect in Client Router
**Severity:** MEDIUM
**Detail:** Redirecting users to URLs parsed directly from query parameters without validation allows phishing redirects.

**Vulnerable Code:**
```react
import React, { useEffect } from 'react';

function LoginRedirect() {
  useEffect(() => {
    const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    const redirectUrl = urlParams.get('next');
    // VULNERABLE: Direct redirect
    if (redirectUrl) {
      window.location.href = redirectUrl;
    }
  }, []);

  return <div>Logging in...</div>;
}
```

**Fixed Code:**
```react
import React, { useEffect } from 'react';

function LoginRedirect() {
  useEffect(() => {
    const urlParams = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    const redirectUrl = urlParams.get('next');

    // FIXED: Enforce relative paths or whitelist domains
    if (redirectUrl) {
      if (redirectUrl.startsWith('/') && !redirectUrl.startsWith('//')) {
        window.location.href = redirectUrl;
      } else {
        console.warn('Unauthorized redirect target');
      }
    }
  }, []);

  return <div>Logging in...</div>;
}
```

**Why This Fix Works:**
Restricting redirects to relative paths starting with a single slash prevent hackers from redirecting users to external phishing sites.

